{"type":"text","timestamp":1780205251809,"sessionID":"ses_1838070fafferbmuIbMyAqlS9c","part":{"id":"prt_e7c806cda001VNTy7gRiktmJ0S","messageID":"msg_e7c805393001qCvxiZutj1B4IF","sessionID":"ses_1838070fafferbmuIbMyAqlS9c","type":"text","text":"Let me check the operator guide for documented invocation:\n","time":{"start":1780205251802,"end":1780205251806}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780205252292,"sessionID":"ses_1838070fafferbmuIbMyAqlS9c","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_o5zkri73drfs_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator_guide.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator_guide.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Lane C — skill-benchmark operator guide\n2: \n3: Lane C benchmarks whether a *skill* is well-routed, discoverable, efficient, and useful **in practice** — distinct from `sk-doc`/`validate.sh` (doc shape) and manual testing playbooks (described behavior). It emits a ranked, remediable Skill Benchmark Report.\n4: \n5: ## Invocation\n6: \n7: ```bash\n8: # Mode A (router-replay, deterministic — the CI gate). Run on a skill that has an\n9: # INTENT_SIGNALS + RESOURCE_MAP smart router in its SKILL.md.\n10: node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n11:   --mode=skill-benchmark \\\n12:   --skill=<skill-id-or-root> \\\n13:   --outputs-dir=<path> \\\n14:   [--fixtures-dir=<path>] [--trace-mode=router]\n15: ```\n16: \n17: Command surface: `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop` (see `commands/deep/start-skill-benchmark-loop.md`).\n18: \n19: ## What runs (Mode A)\n20: \n21: 1. **D5 connectivity** (static, hard gate) — runs first; dead routed paths, dead intent keys, path escapes, orphan refs, unparseable router. Any P0 caps the verdict to `BLOCKED-BY-STRUCTURE`.\n22: 2. **Fixtures** — public/private pairs under `assets/skill-benchmark/fixtures/<skill-id>/` (`<id>.public.json` + `<id>.private.json`).\n23: 3. **Per scenario** — contamination-lint the public prompt (a leak is a fixture failure), then router-replay, then join with private gold to score.\n24: 4. **Report** — `skill-benchmark-report.json` + `skill-benchmark-report.md` (rendered FROM the JSON, anti-drift).\n25: \n26: ## Dimensions\n27: \n28: | Dim | What | Mode A |\n29: | --- | ---- | ------ |\n30: | D1-intra | in-skill router selects expected intents/resources | scored |\n31: | D2 | unprompted discovery (router-replay recall proxy) | scored |\n32: | D3 | efficiency (over-routing proxy) | scored |\n33: | D5 | structural connectivity | scored (hard gate) |\n34: | D1-inter | advisor selects the right skill | unscored (needs live/advisor) |\n35: | D4 | usefulness via skill-on/off ablation | unscored (needs live mode) |\n36: \n37: D1-inter + D4 are deferred to live mode (Mode B) — see the 002 implementation playbook. Mode A is honest about its coverage: the aggregate normalizes over the dimensions actually measured.\n38: \n39: ## Verdict bands (provisional — calibrate on 2-3 pilots)\n40: \n41: `PASS` ≥80 & no gate · `CONDITIONAL` 50–79 · `FAIL` <50 · `BLOCKED-BY-STRUCTURE` on any D5 P0.\n42: \n43: ## Target eligibility\n44: \n45: Mode A needs a parseable `INTENT_SIGNALS` + `RESOURCE_MAP` router (e.g. the `cli-*` skills). Skills without that pattern report `router_unparseable` and gate — that is a real signal that the skill is not smart-router-routable, not a harness bug. A skill that routes via a different mechanism is a candidate for live-mode (Mode B) measurement once built.\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Lane C — skill-benchmark operator guide\n\nLane C benchmarks whether a *skill* is well-routed, discoverable, efficient, and useful **in practice** — distinct from `sk-doc`/`validate.sh` (doc shape) and manual testing playbooks (described behavior). It emits a ranked, remediable Skill Benchmark Report.\n\n## Invocation\n\n```bash\n# Mode A (router-replay, deterministic — the CI gate). Run on a skill that has an\n# INTENT_SIGNALS + RESOURCE_MAP smart router in its SKILL.md.\nnode .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n  --mode=skill-benchmark \\\n  --skill=<skill-id-or-root> \\\n  --outputs-dir=<path> \\\n  [--fixtures-dir=<path>] [--trace-mode=router]\n```\n\nCommand surface: `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop` (see `commands/deep/start-skill-benchmark-loop.md`).\n\n## What runs (Mode A)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/operator_guide.md","time":{"start":1780205252277,"end":1780205252291}},"id":"prt_e7c806cdf001mHhbPd4yXmxhs9","sessionID":"ses_1838070fafferbmuIbMyAqlS9c","messageID":"msg_e7c805393001qCvxiZutj1B4IF"}}
