{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780205318155,"sessionID":"ses_1838070fafferbmuIbMyAqlS9c","part":{"id":"prt_e7c8170080014jQ5jvTj8vx8TC","messageID":"msg_e7c8168c7001q2za4JCG5XrF5j","sessionID":"ses_1838070fafferbmuIbMyAqlS9c","snapshot":"c5a6c058a0dddea3c9d46c8b0edfa25498c05644","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780205322028,"sessionID":"ses_1838070fafferbmuIbMyAqlS9c","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_g94x1m4u0axy_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/scenario_authoring.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/scenario_authoring.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Lane C — scenario (fixture) authoring\n2: \n3: Fixtures are public/private pairs under `assets/skill-benchmark/fixtures/<skill-id>/`:\n4: \n5: - `<scenarioId>.public.json` — dispatched material only. `{ scenarioId, tier, public: { prompt, runtime, mutationBoundary, outputContract }, provenance }`. The `prompt` is written in **domain language** — it must NOT name the skill, its triggers, intent keys, resource paths/basenames, or commands (the contamination linter rejects leaks before scoring).\n6: - `<scenarioId>.private.json` — scorer-only gold, never crosses the dispatch boundary. `{ scenarioId, expected: { skillId, advisorLane, intentKeys, resources, negativeActivation }, rubric }`.\n7: \n8: ## Three tiers (anti-circularity)\n9: \n10: - **T1 — auto-derived + paraphrased.** Gold keys mechanically derived from the skill's own `RESOURCE_MAP[intent]`; prompt paraphrased from the task domain and decontaminated. Breadth/coverage; circular unless decontaminated.\n11: - **T2 — hand-authored holdout.** Prompt written from the task domain by an author blind to `INTENT_SIGNALS`/`RESOURCE_MAP`; gold joined privately. The honesty anchor.\n12: - **T3 — adversarial.** Sibling-skill paraphrases, decoys whose gold belongs to another skill, and \"should NOT activate\" negatives (`negativeActivation: true`).\n13: \n14: Publish the **T1↔T2 score gap** as the circularity meter (mirrors the advisor corpus↔holdout split). A large gap is a finding against the corpus, not evidence the skill is good.\n15: \n16: ## Coverage\n17: \n18: Aim for ≥1 admitted fixture per `INTENT_SIGNALS` key, per `RESOURCE_MAP` target, and per \"When NOT to Use\" class. Uncovered keys are themselves dead-key findings.\n19: \n20: ## Note on empty gold\n21: \n22: `expected.intentKeys`/`expected.resources` may be left `[]` while a skill's router map is still being confirmed; Mode A treats empty gold as non-penalizing (scores structure/efficiency only). Populate from a router-extract pass to get real D1-intra/D2 signal.\n\n(End of file - total 22 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Lane C — scenario (fixture) authoring\n\nFixtures are public/private pairs under `assets/skill-benchmark/fixtures/<skill-id>/`:\n\n- `<scenarioId>.public.json` — dispatched material only. `{ scenarioId, tier, public: { prompt, runtime, mutationBoundary, outputContract }, provenance }`. The `prompt` is written in **domain language** — it must NOT name the skill, its triggers, intent keys, resource paths/basenames, or commands (the contamination linter rejects leaks before scoring).\n- `<scenarioId>.private.json` — scorer-only gold, never crosses the dispatch boundary. `{ scenarioId, expected: { skillId, advisorLane, intentKeys, resources, negativeActivation }, rubric }`.\n\n## Three tiers (anti-circularity)\n\n- **T1 — auto-derived + paraphrased.** Gold keys mechanically derived from the skill's own `RESOURCE_MAP[intent]`; prompt paraphrased from the task domain and decontaminated. Breadth/coverage; circular unless decontaminated.\n- **T2 — hand-authored holdout.** Prompt written from the task domain by an author blind to `INTENT_SIGNALS`/`RESOURCE_MAP`; gold joined privately. The honesty anchor.\n- **T3 — adversarial.** Sibling-skill paraphrases, decoys whose gold belongs to another skill, and \"should NOT activate\" negatives (`negativeActivation: true`).\n\nPublish the **T1↔T2 score gap** as the circularity meter (mirrors the advisor corpus↔holdout split). A large gap is a finding against the corpus, not evidence the skill is good.\n\n## Coverage\n\nAim for ≥1 admitted fixture per `INTENT_SIGNALS` key, per `RESOURCE_MAP` target, and per \"When NOT to Use\" class. Uncovered keys are themselves dead-key findings.\n\n## Note on empty gold","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/references/skill-benchmark/scenario_authoring.md","time":{"start":1780205322004,"end":1780205322027}},"id":"prt_e7c817e95001mW0b1yskejScJq","sessionID":"ses_1838070fafferbmuIbMyAqlS9c","messageID":"msg_e7c8168c7001q2za4JCG5XrF5j"}}
